 Tong Tong, I'll be honest. 

67
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:39,260
 I do have the money, 

68
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:41,900
 but it’s all in the bank earning interest. 

69
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:42,940
 That's ¥200,000. 

70
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,700
 The interest is almost ¥10,000 a year. 

71
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,020
 Don't take this the wrong way, 

72
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:50,740
 but if I lend it to you, I'll lose the interest. 

73
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:53,180
 And I don't know when I’ll get the principal back. 

74
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:57,740
 Also, I heard your uncle is suing you. 

75
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:00,380
Auntie, how about this?

76
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:02,540
I'll borrow ¥200,000 from you. I'll repay ¥10,000 every year,

77
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:03,860
¥3,000 more than the bank interest.

78
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:06,100
The bank only pays interest at maturity,

79
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:09,180
but I can make monthly payments.

80
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,460
Right now, it'd be ¥2,000 a month.

81
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,700
Once I get a job, I can even repay more.

82
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,020
I’ll repay all in two years at most.

83
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:15,540
Is that okay with you?

84
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:17,220
 Words aren't enough. 

85
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:18,380
I'm begging you, Auntie.

86
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:19,540
Then how about this?

87
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:21,880
I'll write an IOU and send you a photo of it.

88
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,140
 All right. 

89
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:26,180
 Listen, I'm helping you only because we're related. 

90
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:29,060
- Okay. 
 -  I wouldn't even bother for anyone else. 

91
00:05:29,060 --> 00:05:31,300
 Oh, don't let your cousin, He Jin, know 

92
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,820
 that I'm lending you the money. 

93
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:35,780
 You know, if he finds out about this money, 

94
00:05:35,780 --> 00:05:38,180
 he will surely covet it and gamble it away. 

95
00:05:38,180 --> 00:05:40,780
Understood. Thank you, Auntie.

96
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:42,660
I'll write the IOU now.

97
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:44,980
 All right. 

98
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:56,980
 Ding Zhi Tong, wake up now. 

99
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:58,980
 You have no time for a relationship right now. 

100
00:05:58,980 --> 00:06:01,240
 Focus on making money. 

101
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:22,420
Tong Tong, you got your computer fixed?

102
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:23,940
Gan Yang helped me with it.

103
00:06:23,940 --> 00:06:25,980
What's wrong? Is there a problem?

104
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,940
No.

105
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:31,220
 He basically replaced all the hardware. 

106
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:35,160
Here's the money for Ding Zhi Tong's computer repair and replaced parts.

107
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,050
Did she send you to me?

108
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:41,340
Why doesn't she repay me herself?

109
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:43,060
We're all adults.

110
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:44,940
Her message is very clear.

111
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,860
Please don't bother her from now on.

112
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:50,020
What's your relationship with her?

113
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:53,180
Take the money.

114
00:07:03,620 --> 00:07:04,972
- Done. 
 - Thanks.

115
00:07:04,972 --> 00:07:06,580
Thank you.

116
00:07:07,925 --> 00:07:09,150
   

117
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,690
Hello?

118
00:07:18,690 --> 00:07:20,700
Tong Tong, what's the matter?

119
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:23,780
Mom, why did it take you so long to answer?

120
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,180
I-I was dancing in the park.

121
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:29,420
It's too crowded and noisy. I couldn't hear you.

122
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,780
I got my salary this month.

123
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:33,520
Guess how much I got?

124
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,220
- Is it 2,500? 
 - It's 3,000.

125
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:37,640
Really 3,000?

126
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,760
That much?

127
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:42,100
My boss said I did well this month.

128
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,940
Besides the ¥2,500 salary,

129
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:45,660
I got a ¥500 bonus.

130
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:48,100
I'll repay ¥2,000 to Aun...

131
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,920
I mean, repay ¥2,000 to Uncle and send ¥500 to you.

132
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:53,460
No need. I haven't even spent all the money you gave me last month.

133
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:54,780
 I don't need money this month. 

134
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,520
 Besides, ¥500 isn't enough for you. 

135
00:07:56,520 --> 00:08:00,360
Use the extra money to treat yourself to a nice dress. Don't skimp.

136
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,460
I'm doing fine. Don't worry.

137
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:04,820
Ma'am, how much for the pancake?

138
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,660
One moment, please.

139
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:11,220
Mom, are you selling pancakes on the street again?

140
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:14,340
No. I was just passing someone's stall.

141
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:16,700
Then let's have a video call now?

142
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,180
I’m just at home with nothing to do.

143
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:20,820
Thought I'd give it a try.

144
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:23,060
Consider that as killing time.

145
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:26,180
Mom, the doctor said you need rest.

146
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:27,780
Pack everything at once,

147
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:30,500
or I'll take leave and come help you.

148
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,060
All right, I got it.

149
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:33,780
I'm packing up now.

150
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,100
Keep your word.

151
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:37,580
Okay, all right. I got it.

152
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:39,140
Hold on, please.

153
00:08:39,140 --> 00:08:43,700
Mom, we will have a better life someday.

154
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:47,580
Once I start earning more, I’ll take you on a trip,

155
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:49,860
all over the country.

156
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:52,720
 All right then. 

157
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,500
 I'm hanging up. 

158
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,540
The call is expensive.

159
00:08:57,540 --> 00:09:00,500
Okay, bye bye.

160
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:04,080
Ma’am, your daughter is so good to you.

161
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,780
- Sorry about that. 
 - No worries.

162
00:09:09,860 --> 00:09:12,780
Things will get better for us.

163
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:17,940
Ding Zhi Tong!

164
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:20,100
Senior.

165
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,460
How is it? Is the computer working well?

166
00:09:22,460 --> 00:09:23,860
It's quite good.

167
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:25,020
Of course, it is.

168
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:26,340
Let me tell you a secret.

169
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:29,760
Gan Yang replaced all your laptop's parts.

170
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:34,300
Do you know how much it cost?

171
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:36,140
It was 2,000.

172
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:37,220
He made me promise not to tell.

173
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:39,100
Don't tell him I said anything.

174
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,980
But you need to appreciate what he’s done for you.

175
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:42,700
I need to get to the lab.

176
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:44,440
Bye bye.

177
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:01,620
Auntie, well, I really need to apologize.

178
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:04,080
But can I delay the first payment by a month?

179
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,060
 What? 

180
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:07,180
 You promised you’d start repaying this month. 

181
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:09,420
 You’re backing out before you’ve even started? 

182
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:11,100
 No wonder nobody else would lend you money. 

183
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:13,060
I'm sorry, Auntie.

184
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:14,540
Something unexpected came up.

185
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:16,820
I'll surely start the payment next month.

186
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:18,420
 If you break your word again next month, 

187
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:19,840
 I won't lend you any money again. 

188
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,380
Understood. Thank you, Auntie.

