190
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,260
Hello?

191
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:43,840
I have to speak to you in person. Let's meet.

192
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:52,720
Ding Zhi Tong.

193
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:57,580
Did you ask Feng Sheng to repay me for the laptop?

194
00:11:03,620 --> 00:11:08,340
Are you distancing yourself from me?

195
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:13,640
I appreciate your fixing my computer, but I don't like owing people.

196
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,160
"People"?

197
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,860
Am I considered "people" to you?

198
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:20,640
No matter what,

199
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:23,220
I owe you a thank you.

200
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:27,500
I should go.

201
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:32,980
 Gan Yang, I know you're kind to me. 

202
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:36,000
 But I can't give you what you're looking for right now. 

203
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,260
   

204
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:09,980
Tong Tong.

205
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:11,420
Feng Sheng.

206
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:14,220
Thank you for helping me repay Gan Yang.

207
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:16,540
Did you see him?

208
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:18,760
Is he returning the money to me?

209
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,380
No. I saved it from my part-time job.

210
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:25,020
You realized he replaced my computer parts, right?

211
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:30,940
I’ve noticed you work hard at your part-time job.

212
00:12:30,940 --> 00:12:33,780
I didn't want to put too much pressure on you.

213
00:12:33,780 --> 00:12:35,340
Thanks.

214
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:37,500
Come on, Ding Zhi Tong.

215
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,540
We've known each other for years.

216
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:40,120
Do you really need to be so formal?

217
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,500
Just take it.

218
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,940
Take it.

219
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:51,040
By the way, have you heard back from Hetai Securities?

220
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,180
It doesn't look promising.

221
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:56,820
Have you applied to other companies?

222
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,080
I tried Moqi Investment.

223
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,540
I'm still waiting to hear.

224
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:01,580
"Moqi Investment"?

225
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:04,720
I thought you'd like a job in Shanghai to be closer to home.

226
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,980
I think Moqi Investment's headquarters is in Beijing.

227
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:10,980
They have a Shanghai Branch which isn't hiring this year.

228
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:12,940
Moqi Investment's salary and benefits are quite good.

229
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:16,500
I thought if nothing works out here,

230
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:21,680
I'll go to Moqi Investment first, then find how to return here.

231
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,720
It's not a bad plan.

232
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,040
What does this mean?

233
00:13:36,180 --> 00:13:38,996
- What did you get? 
 - They're all the same.

234
00:13:38,996 --> 00:13:42,780
These companies are for your mock due-diligence reports.

235
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:45,700
Assume we have ¥20 million in cash.

236
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:49,700
You have one week to conduct your mock due diligence.

237
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:54,260
In a week, your report decides if and how to invest.

238
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:56,780
Professor, only company names are included,

239
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:58,060
no contact information.

240
00:13:58,060 --> 00:13:59,580
How are we supposed to reach them?

241
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:01,320
You have to find your own way.

242
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,620
It's also part of the assessment.

243
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:05,980
Guess we can't contact them.

244
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:08,420
There's not even a phone number.

245
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,550
Quiet.

246
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:12,020
   

247
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,500
Your project is quite difficult.

248
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,860
Due diligence is all about connections.

249
00:14:14,860 --> 00:14:17,060
- You need to understand a company's core business. 
 - Thanks.

250
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:18,880
So it works only if you know the top executives.

251
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:20,280
Thank you.

252
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:21,780
That's my girl.

253
00:14:21,780 --> 00:14:23,500
You don’t evade and get straight to the point.

254
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,834
- What would you like? 
 - Auntie, cauliflower, please.

255
00:14:25,834 --> 00:14:27,500
- Sure. 
 - Me, too.

256
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,760
I tell you, Qin Chang is an oddball.

257
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,140
When I see him, I get annoyed.

258
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:33,900
I really don't want to attend his class anymore.

259
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:34,840
I hate him.

260
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,620
I want more cauliflower, please, Auntie.

261
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:37,820
Sure.

262
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:39,660
Hello, Professor Qin.

263
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:41,140
Hello.

264
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:46,620
Professor Qin, what a coincidence.

265
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:49,080
